pageContext.claim: “I want to express our gratitude to each of your countries [Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania] for fulfilling your full obligations and meeting the 2 percent GDP benchmark for national defense this year.”
pageContext.analysis: Estonia met the 2 percent guideline in 2017. Latvia is projected to join meet it in 2018 — joining the six countries who already meet the requirement. Lithuania, however, is not ontrack to meet the NATO guideline in 2018.
